1
0:00:09,050 --> 0:00:18,160
瞧 看这创世以来 拥有更多奇迹的世界
Look, see a world that holds more wonders than any since the Earth was born.

2
0:00:20,430 --> 0:00:30,340
一切作王者 没人名如那从石中拔剑的男孩
And of all who reigned o'er, none had renown like the boy who pulled sword from stone.

3
0:00:31,980 --> 0:00:39,080
但这不是关于那国王 也不是他的歌
But this is not that king...nor is this his song.

4
0:00:40,990 --> 0:00:44,090
让我告诉你一个新的故事
Let me tell you instead a new tale.

5
0:00:44,160 --> 0:00:47,190
我将讲述它 如同我曾听闻
I'll lay it down as I've heard it told.

6
0:00:47,260 --> 0:00:53,800
寄出它的信 追溯它的历史 这是一次勇敢无畏的冒险
Its letters sent, its history pressed, of an adventure brave and bold.

7
0:00:53,870 --> 0:01:01,670
永远地 记于心 铭于石 如同一切伟大的古老神话
Forever set, in heart, in stone, like all great myths of old.

8
0:03:06,830 --> 0:03:08,130
基督诞生了
Christ is born.

9
0:03:11,540 --> 0:03:13,070
基督当然诞生了
Christ is born indeed.

10
0:03:24,280 --> 0:03:25,590
你要去哪
Where are you going?

11
0:03:25,650 --> 0:03:27,150
去教堂
To church!

12
0:03:27,650 --> 0:03:29,020
为什么
Why?

13
0:03:32,690 --> 0:03:35,160
我的靴子 你好啊 艾格尼丝
My boots. Hello, Agnes.

14
0:03:36,500 --> 0:03:37,960
我的靴子在哪
Where are my boots?

15
0:03:45,470 --> 0:03:46,910
你是一名骑士了吗
You a knight yet?

16
0:03:46,970 --> 0:03:47,970
什么
What?

17
0:03:48,040 --> 0:03:49,470
你是骑士了吗
You a knight yet?

18
0:03:50,340 --> 0:03:52,540
- 还不是 - 最好赶紧地
- Not yet. - Better hurry up.

19
0:03:52,610 --> 0:03:54,480
我有的是时间
I've got time.

20
0:03:55,450 --> 0:03:57,150
我有的是很多时间
I've got lots of time.

21
0:03:58,120 --> 0:04:00,220
嘿 埃塞尔
Hey! Essel.

22
0:04:02,090 --> 0:04:03,890
- 嘿 慢点 - 赶紧的
- Hey, slow down. - Hurry up!

23
0:04:03,960 --> 0:04:05,290
埃塞尔
Essel.

24
0:04:06,730 --> 0:04:08,660
埃塞尔
Essel.

25
0:04:08,730 --> 0:04:12,100
我们就待在这吧 来 我们就待在这吧
Let's just stay here. Come on. Let's just stay here.

26
0:04:14,970 --> 0:04:16,570
- 起来 - 不
- Get up. - No.

27
0:04:17,340 --> 0:04:18,870
我还没准备好
I'm not ready yet.

28
0:04:20,740 --> 0:04:22,170
我还没准备好
I'm not ready.

29
0:04:27,950 --> 0:04:29,580
圣诞快乐 格林格洛
Merry Christmas, Gryngelot.

30
0:05:32,340 --> 0:05:33,750
你去哪了
Where have you been?

31
0:05:33,810 --> 0:05:34,980
做弥撒
At Mass.

32
0:05:35,050 --> 0:05:37,920
- 你 去做弥撒了 - 是的
- You, at Mass? - Yeah.

33
0:05:37,980 --> 0:05:39,350
一整夜
All night?

34
0:05:40,590 --> 0:05:42,050
是的
Yes.

35
0:05:42,120 --> 0:05:43,720
那好 你的靴子呢
Well, where are your boots?

36
0:05:44,290 --> 0:05:45,460
什么
What?

37
0:05:45,520 --> 0:05:47,690
你的
Where are...

38
0:05:51,130 --> 0:05:52,930
你闻着像是做了弥撒
You do smell like you've been at Mass.

39
0:05:53,000 --> 0:05:56,170
怎么了 你整晚都在喝圣餐吗
What, have you been drinking the sacrament all night?

40
0:05:56,230 --> 0:05:58,240
我爱你 妈妈
I love you, Mother.

41
0:06:22,130 --> 0:06:23,500
你还没着装
You are not dressed.

42
0:06:24,630 --> 0:06:27,830
今年我没有寻欢作乐的心力
I've got no guts for merriment this year.

43
0:06:27,900 --> 0:06:29,300
但这是圣诞日
But it's Christmas.

44
0:06:29,370 --> 0:06:34,540
会有更多圣诞日的 更多盛宴 更多好消息
There'll be more Christmases, more feasts, more glad tidings.

45
0:06:40,180 --> 0:06:42,620
你去吧 找点乐子
You go, make merry.

46
0:06:45,020 --> 0:06:46,590
再告诉我你所见所闻
And tell me what you see.

47
0:08:43,870 --> 0:08:46,370
把小高文带来
Bring young Gawain here.

48
0:08:53,680 --> 0:08:55,750
国王要和你谈谈
The king would speak with you.

49
0:09:33,850 --> 0:09:36,020
你妈妈在哪
Where is thy mother?

50
0:09:36,090 --> 0:09:38,820
她感到不舒服 殿下
She was not feeling herself, my lord.

51
0:09:40,060 --> 0:09:44,260
那就过来 坐这里 挨着我们
Then come. Sit here, besides us.

52
0:09:44,330 --> 0:09:46,330
挨着我和王后
Besides me and my queen.

53
0:09:48,600 --> 0:09:49,870
那不是属于我的位置
That is not my place.

54
0:09:51,540 --> 0:09:55,010
不 今天就随它去吧
No. Let it be, today.

55
0:09:56,040 --> 0:09:58,610
它的主人不在
Its owner is away.

56
0:09:58,680 --> 0:10:00,810
谁知道他什么时候回来呢
Who knows when he will return?

57
0:10:02,920 --> 0:10:04,420
请吧
Please.

58
0:10:13,090 --> 0:10:16,060
很高兴见到你 高文
Good to see you, Gawain.

59
0:10:16,130 --> 0:10:20,900
有家人在身旁真好
Good to have one's family by one's side.

60
0:10:22,940 --> 0:10:23,970
血脉
One's blood.

61
0:10:25,400 --> 0:10:30,810
你的骑士们以你的名义流了足够多的血 他们比我更亲近于你
Surely your knights have spilled enough blood in your name to bind them closer to you than I.

62
0:10:31,410 --> 0:10:32,710
对
True.

63
0:10:34,780 --> 0:10:40,350
但你是我姐姐的孩子 由她的子宫生出
But you are my sister's boy, queefed from her womb.

64
0:10:42,020 --> 0:10:44,090
他们不是
They are not.

65
0:10:44,160 --> 0:10:58,600
今天在这里 我看着我的朋友们 我看到了 所有缪斯都不曾唱或梦见的歌
I look out upon my friends here today and I see... songs...no muse could ever sing or dream of.

66
0:11:01,910 --> 0:11:04,380
但我看向你 却看到了什么
But I turn to thee and I see what?

67
0:11:05,610 --> 0:11:10,150
我认识你 却不了解你
I recognize but I do not know thee.

68
0:11:10,220 --> 0:11:23,560
我说这些不是责备 而是在遗憾 我不曾让你坐在我身边 直到今天 或者在你出生不久 能伏在我膝头
I say this not in reproach, but regret that I have never asked you to sit at my side before this day or upon my knee when thy was newborn.

69
0:11:26,730 --> 0:11:32,500
但今天是圣诞日 我想搭起桥梁
But now it is Christmas, and I wish to build bridges.

70
0:11:35,210 --> 0:11:43,380
所以在我们寻乐子前 你为我准备一份礼物吧
So before we make merry...you make for me a gift.

71
0:11:44,820 --> 0:11:49,860
你告诉我一个关于你的故事 好让我了解你
You tell me a tale of yourself, so that I might know thee.

72
0:12:05,640 --> 0:12:07,940
我没有什么好讲的 殿下
I have none to tell, King.

73
0:12:10,480 --> 0:12:11,910
还没有
Yet.

74
0:12:13,850 --> 0:12:15,950
你还没有什么要讲的
You have none to tell yet.

75
0:12:18,180 --> 0:12:19,590
还没有
Yet.

76
0:12:20,490 --> 0:12:22,190
看看你周围 小高文
Look around you, young Gawain.

77
0:12:24,160 --> 0:12:25,460
你看到了什么
What do you see?

78
0:12:32,600 --> 0:12:34,070
我看到了传说们
I see legends.

79
0:12:36,570 --> 0:12:39,040
不要在他们中间无所事事
Do not take your place amongst them idly.

80
0:12:41,640 --> 0:12:42,940
嗯
Hmm.

81
0:12:50,380 --> 0:12:54,990
那么接着到谁 嗯
So who else then... hmm?

82
0:13:00,660 --> 0:13:02,130
朋友们
Friends...

83
0:13:07,170 --> 0:13:13,810
兄弟 兄弟们和 姐妹们
Brothers... (Brothers...) Brothers and... sisters all. (…sisters all)

84
0:13:14,970 --> 0:13:21,480
我感谢你们在受福之日与我分食面包
I thank thee for breaking bread with me this blessed day.

85
0:13:22,610 --> 0:13:40,530
它是神圣的 因为今早我望向窗外 我看到了由你们双手所塑的土地的形状
And it is blessed... for out my window this morn I looked, and I saw a land shaped...by your hands.

86
0:13:43,770 --> 0:13:55,010
你们以同样的手伸向我们撒克逊的弟兄们 如今在你们的阴影下 他们像婴孩般低头
You have lain those same hands upon our Saxon brethren, who now in your shadow bow their heads like babes.

87
0:13:55,080 --> 0:14:17,570
和平 这由你们为你们的王国带来的和平 所以在这和平里 我此刻告诉你们 我是最幸之人 因为我在你们中间
Peace, peace you have brought to your kingdom, so it is in peace that I... I now say to you... that I... I am the luckiest here today...because I am amongst thee.

88
0:14:21,210 --> 0:14:22,880
我与你们同在
I am amongst thee.

89
0:14:25,910 --> 0:14:38,220
所以在我们庆祝我们的基督诞生前 让我们敬奉他的名行了大事的我们每一个人
So before we celebrate the birth of our Christ, let us honor one of our own who has done great things in His name.

90
0:14:39,730 --> 0:14:45,300
所以说一个故事 或者 或者一场表演
So a tale, or... Or a show perhaps.

91
0:14:45,360 --> 0:14:46,600
你们有什么
What have thee?

92
0:14:48,700 --> 0:15:00,280
谁能用关于你们自己的神话或篇章来取悦我和王后
Who can regale me and my queen with some myth or canto of thine own purport?

93
0:15:37,620 --> 0:15:39,620
等等
Hold.

94
0:17:20,220 --> 0:17:27,020
噢 最伟大的国王 让我沉浸在这友好的圣诞游戏中吧
Oh, Greatest Of Kings, indulge me in this friendly Christmas game.

95
0:17:27,090 --> 0:17:36,900
让你的骑士中 最勇猛最不羁的人站出来 拿起武器 试着光荣地给我一击
Let whichever of your knights is boldest of blood and wildest of heart step forth, take up arms, and try with honor to land a blow against me.

96
0:17:36,970 --> 0:17:42,010
无论谁伤了我 都将拥有这个 我的武器
Whomsoever nicks me shall lay claim to this, my arm.

97
0:17:42,070 --> 0:17:45,610
它的荣耀和财富将属于你
It's glory and riches shall be thine.

98
0:17:45,680 --> 0:17:47,050
但是
But...

99
0:17:49,310 --> 0:17:52,850
你的冠军必须遵守这点:
thy champ must bind himself to this:

100
0:17:53,750 --> 0:18:03,460
要是他给了一击 那么一年后的圣诞 他必须到那边去找我 往北行6日 到绿教堂
Should he land a blow, then one year and Yuletide hence, he must seek me out yonder, to the Green Chapel six nights to the North.

101
0:18:03,530 --> 0:18:07,530
他会在那发现我 他要屈膝 让我回敬他一击
He shall find me there and bend the knee and let me strike him in return.

102
0:18:07,600 --> 0:18:17,410
无论是脸颊上的划痕 还是喉咙上的割伤 我都将以牙还牙 然后凭信任和友谊 我们就此别过
Be it a scratch on the cheek or a cut on the throat, I will return what was given to me, and then in trust and friendship we shall part.

103
0:18:17,480 --> 0:18:21,510
那么 谁愿同我打赌呢
Who, then, who is willing to engage with me?

104
0:18:26,790 --> 0:18:28,490
醒醒 女王
Help. Queen.

105
0:18:52,040 --> 0:18:54,050
这是你自己的挑战吗
This challenge is thine own?

106
0:18:58,690 --> 0:19:06,830
虽然我的意志渴望跃过这张桌子去面对你 但我的身体却无法跟随
Though my will longs to leap across this table and meet thee, my body will not follow.

107
0:19:11,430 --> 0:19:22,370
我们中一定有人愿意面对这位骑士 按照他的条件
Surely there is one amongst us here who will meet this knight on his terms.

108
0:19:25,780 --> 0:19:27,280
我会的
I will do it.

109
0:19:28,950 --> 0:19:30,420
我会面对他
I will meet him.

110
0:19:33,920 --> 0:19:35,320
我将面对你
I will meet thee.

111
0:19:38,890 --> 0:19:41,590
你明白这个挑战吗
You understand this challenge?

112
0:19:41,660 --> 0:19:42,890
我明白
I do.

113
0:19:45,960 --> 0:19:47,330
我想我明白
I think I do.

114
0:19:53,340 --> 0:19:56,510
记住 这只是一场游戏
Remember, it is only a game.

115
0:20:10,420 --> 0:20:11,590
我需要一把剑
I need a sword.

116
0:20:16,190 --> 0:20:17,830
我需要 我需要一把剑
I need... I need a sword.

117
0:20:17,900 --> 0:20:19,930
高文
Gawain.

118
0:21:06,240 --> 0:21:07,650
来吧 绿骑士
Have at me, Green Knight.

119
0:21:25,360 --> 0:21:27,300
行动吧 不然我要行动了
Make a move or I shall make mine.

120
0:21:44,980 --> 0:21:46,380
这是什么
What is this?

121
0:21:47,050 --> 0:21:48,420
一个诡计
A trick?

122
0:21:52,160 --> 0:21:53,730
站起来 面对我
Stand up and face me!

123
0:22:05,300 --> 0:22:06,970
你期待我怎么做
What do you expect me to do?

124
0:22:07,040 --> 0:22:08,740
拿出勇气
Have courage.

125
0:22:21,190 --> 0:22:22,520
很好
Very well.

126
0:22:26,660 --> 0:22:28,030
很好
Very well.

127
0:22:29,360 --> 0:22:31,260
你搁下了挑战
You laid down your challenge.

128
0:22:33,700 --> 0:22:36,640
我接受了 现在也接受
I accepted it and I accept it still.

129
0:22:39,670 --> 0:22:44,880
永远别忘记这个圣诞日 在这里发生的一切
Never forget what happened here upon this Christmas Day!

130
0:23:50,080 --> 0:23:55,280
一年后
One year hence...

131
0:26:04,740 --> 0:26:06,580
那是什么感觉
What did it feel like?

132
0:26:14,390 --> 0:26:17,290
那是什么感觉 当你
What did it feel like when you...

133
0:26:19,490 --> 0:26:24,600
就像把瓜切半
Like cutting a melon in two.

134
0:26:26,930 --> 0:26:28,970
那么那是什么感觉
And what does that feel like?

135
0:26:31,570 --> 0:26:33,070
没什么感觉
Like nothing.

136
0:26:39,010 --> 0:26:40,380
你害怕了吗
Were you afraid?

137
0:26:42,180 --> 0:26:43,180
不
No.

138
0:26:43,250 --> 0:26:44,750
那么你就是说说吗
Are you just saying that?

139
0:26:47,450 --> 0:26:49,760
我还在在这里 而他不在
I am here, and he is not.

140
0:26:58,260 --> 0:27:02,700
国王把他的剑借给我了 你知道吗
The king lent me his sword, did you know that?

141
0:27:03,900 --> 0:27:04,770
你握着它
You held it?

142
0:27:04,840 --> 0:27:06,970
是的 我不只握着它
Well, I did more than hold it.

143
0:27:08,570 --> 0:27:20,120
看啊 勇敢的高文阁下 斩首如切瓜 谁也不能 得到它了
Behold, Brave Sir Gawain, chopper of heads...severer of melons, who cannot...get it up.

144
0:27:47,980 --> 0:27:50,380
你是高文 是吗
You're Gawain, aren't you?

145
0:27:50,450 --> 0:27:53,350
不 你肯定搞错了
Nah, you must be mistaken.

146
0:27:53,420 --> 0:27:55,860
不 不 你就是他
No, no, you're him.

147
0:27:55,920 --> 0:27:59,760
你总在这里 几乎都在
You're always here. Always about.

148
0:27:59,830 --> 0:28:03,130
大多数晚上几乎没站稳离开过
Scarcely leave upright most nights.

149
0:28:03,200 --> 0:28:05,870
又不是在圣诞日
But not on Christmas.

150
0:28:05,930 --> 0:28:07,600
你听说过吗
Have you heard?

151
0:28:07,670 --> 0:28:11,240
这个男孩杀了绿骑士
This boy slew the Green Knight.

152
0:28:11,300 --> 0:28:17,880
用他自己的斧头 他砍下巨人的头 而现在他和我们一起喝酒
With his own axe, he lopped off the giant's head, and now he drinks with us!

153
0:28:18,980 --> 0:28:20,980
但他妈妈是个女巫
But his mother's a witch.

154
0:29:15,900 --> 0:29:17,140
起身
Rise.

155
0:29:18,200 --> 0:29:19,540
起身
Rise.

156
0:29:23,080 --> 0:29:24,180
坐下
Sit.

157
0:29:31,950 --> 0:29:34,190
我一直在等你
I've been waiting for you.

158
0:29:36,620 --> 0:29:38,860
你没听见我的呼唤吗
Did you not hear me calling?

159
0:30:06,090 --> 0:30:07,850
我的牙疼
My tooth hurts.

160
0:30:12,620 --> 0:30:14,860
又一年已快过去了
Another year nearly gone already.

161
0:30:16,760 --> 0:30:19,530
你想过圣诞日到来前 你要做什么吗
Have you thought what you will do when Christmas comes?

162
0:30:22,400 --> 0:30:24,170
那不就是一场游戏吗
Was it not just a game?

163
0:30:26,500 --> 0:30:28,040
也许是
Perhaps.

164
0:30:29,310 --> 0:30:31,080
但它还没有圆满
But it is not complete.

165
0:30:36,820 --> 0:30:45,760
你真的相信他会坐教堂里 数着日子 消磨一年等着我的到来吗
You truly believe he's sitting in a chapel, counting the hours, whiling away the year waiting for me to come?

166
0:30:47,360 --> 0:30:49,260
好吧 我不知道
Well, I do not know.

167
0:30:52,230 --> 0:30:53,800
你要告诉我
You will tell me.

168
0:30:54,900 --> 0:30:56,840
你必须找到他
You must seek him out.

169
0:30:57,670 --> 0:31:00,510
但如果死亡在等我呢
And if death awaits me?

170
0:31:00,570 --> 0:31:05,180
噢 我确实不知道会有谁在时辰到前 前去迎接死亡
Oh, I do not know of any man who has not marched up to greet death before his time.

171
0:31:10,720 --> 0:31:12,850
你为什么要为我指明道路
Why are you holding me to this light?

172
0:31:19,830 --> 0:31:25,000
对你而言 想要伟大是错的吗
Is it wrong to want greatness for you?

173
0:31:26,970 --> 0:31:29,700
我怕我生来就不是伟大之人
I fear I am not meant for greatness.

174
0:31:32,070 --> 0:31:33,110
嗯
Mm.

175
0:32:10,480 --> 0:32:12,610
在你脸上有泥土
You have mud on your face.

176
0:34:12,460 --> 0:34:19,100
愿圣母保佑你的五指强健 五官敏锐
May the Blessed Virgin keep your five fingers strong, your five senses sharp.

177
0:34:19,170 --> 0:34:22,170
愿她的五种快乐激励你
May her five joys inspire you.

178
0:34:22,240 --> 0:34:25,540
其子的五个伤口予你热情
The five wounds of her son give you fervor.

179
0:34:25,610 --> 0:34:29,110
骑士的五种美德会照亮你的道路
And the five virtues of a knight light your way.

180
0:34:30,320 --> 0:34:32,990
遵守你的约定吧 小高文
Keep thy covenant, young Gawain.

181
0:34:33,050 --> 0:34:35,490
如果上帝朝你微笑
And if God smiles on thee,

182
0:34:37,520 --> 0:34:39,360
那是盼你归来
then hurry thee back.

183
0:34:41,060 --> 0:34:43,900
我们身旁的座位等候你
Thy seat besides us waits.

184
0:34:57,910 --> 0:34:59,910
你真的要去吗
Are you really going to go?

185
0:35:00,650 --> 0:35:01,980
我应该吗
Should I?

186
0:35:03,250 --> 0:35:06,080
我更喜欢你现在的脑袋
I like your head better where it is.

187
0:35:06,150 --> 0:35:09,250
我承诺了 我立下了约定
I gave my word. I made a covenant.

188
0:35:09,320 --> 0:35:13,230
这就是愚蠢的人之所以丧命
This is how silly men perish.

189
0:35:13,290 --> 0:35:15,560
或者勇敢的人之所以变得伟大
Or how brave men become great.

190
0:35:15,630 --> 0:35:17,130
为什么要伟大
Why greatness?

191
0:35:18,730 --> 0:35:20,500
为什么善良还不足够
Why is goodness not enough?

192
0:35:29,510 --> 0:35:31,280
现在拿上这个
Take this now.

193
0:35:33,610 --> 0:35:36,820
离开时把它系在腰间
Wear it about your waist as you go.

194
0:35:38,320 --> 0:35:42,420
- 如果你回来时还戴着它 - 我能回来吗
- And if you wear it still when you return... - Will I return?

195
0:35:42,490 --> 0:35:48,060
你回来时 你一定要昂首阔步
When you return, you will come with your head held high.

196
0:35:48,130 --> 0:35:52,130
我保证 你不会受到伤害
I promise, you will not come to harm.

197
0:35:54,570 --> 0:35:56,200
还有 孩子
And, boy...

198
0:35:58,440 --> 0:36:03,440
我的孩子 不要浪费这机会
My boy... do not waste this.

199
0:36:20,160 --> 0:36:22,930
高文 高文
Gawain! Gawain!

200
0:36:24,830 --> 0:36:26,370
我得到了一把剑
I've got a sword!

201
0:36:30,870 --> 0:36:34,170
加文 伟大之流
Gawain! Great tide.

202
0:36:36,810 --> 0:36:38,810
祝你好运
Good luck!

203
0:36:38,880 --> 0:36:41,150
祝你好运 高文
Good luck, Gawain!

204
0:38:12,000 --> 0:38:13,610
你还喜欢我吗
Do you still fancy me?

205
0:38:16,640 --> 0:38:18,210
我让你快乐吗
Do I make you happy?

206
0:38:20,910 --> 0:38:22,850
是的
Yes.

207
0:38:22,920 --> 0:38:27,420
即使我在这 你在那
Even though I'm here and you're there?

208
0:38:29,990 --> 0:38:31,420
是的
Yes.

209
0:38:34,090 --> 0:38:37,030
如果我请求你让我做你的夫人 你会怎么说
What will you say if I asked you to make me your lady?

210
0:38:38,560 --> 0:38:40,600
- 一位夫人 - 你的夫人
- A lady? - Your lady.

211
0:38:43,770 --> 0:38:46,670
我可以给你比任何夫人都多的金子
I could give you more gold than any lady has.

212
0:38:46,740 --> 0:38:49,310
我已经有你的金子了
I already have your gold.

213
0:38:54,350 --> 0:39:03,390
如果我想坐在你身边 握住你的手 还有 听你的声音呢
What if I wanted to sit by your side and... take your hand and... have your ear?

214
0:39:05,020 --> 0:39:06,730
你会怎么说
What will you say to that?

215
0:39:16,940 --> 0:39:18,500
为什么 当然 埃塞尔
"Why, yes, Essel.

216
0:39:18,570 --> 0:39:20,540
我非常乐意
"I'd like that very much.

217
0:39:22,810 --> 0:39:27,210
我的耳朵 我的手 我的心都归你了
"You may have my ear and my hand and heart.

218
0:39:29,110 --> 0:39:33,050
我会是国王 而你是王后
"And I will be king and you my queen.

219
0:39:34,950 --> 0:39:36,790
你会是我的夫人
"You'll be my lady...

220
0:39:38,990 --> 0:39:40,490
我会是你的男人
"and I'll be your man."

221
0:42:16,380 --> 0:42:17,880
你是谁
Who are you?

222
0:42:19,380 --> 0:42:21,420
只是个旅行者 朋友
Just a traveler, friend.

223
0:42:21,490 --> 0:42:23,220
你看起来像名骑士
You look like a knight.

224
0:42:24,490 --> 0:42:26,630
我只是经过
Just passing through.

225
0:42:26,690 --> 0:42:30,330
啊 我猜你想要分享一些东西 对吧
Ah. I take it you'll want some of the shares, so, huh?

226
0:42:31,060 --> 0:42:32,800
一些什么
Of what?

227
0:42:32,870 --> 0:42:34,300
所有的这些
All of this!

228
0:42:36,770 --> 0:42:38,470
为什么他们没有被埋葬
Why weren't they buried?

229
0:42:38,540 --> 0:42:41,940
都死了 都死了
All dead. All dead.

230
0:42:42,010 --> 0:42:43,580
没人埋葬他们
No one to bury 'em.

231
0:42:43,640 --> 0:42:47,110
不过你知道 大自然会有办法的
Though you know, nature will do its trick.

232
0:42:47,180 --> 0:42:50,250
她会吸它们 然后塞紧
She'll suck 'em in and tuck 'em tight.

233
0:42:52,990 --> 0:42:57,620
诶 话这么说 我有两个兄弟在这以外的什么地方
Eh, in saying that, I do have two brothers out here somewhere.

234
0:42:59,890 --> 0:43:03,100
他们出走了 他们再没回家
And they marched off. They never came home.

235
0:43:03,160 --> 0:43:07,600
你要直到 如果不是因为我妈 我早就来这了 我早就来这了
You know, if it weren't for my ma, I would've been here. I would've been here!

236
0:43:07,670 --> 0:43:09,100
我也会在这里
I would've been here too!

237
0:43:10,670 --> 0:43:12,640
他们都在这里了
They all came here!

238
0:43:15,410 --> 0:43:17,010
虽然我会撑得久一点
Though I'd have lasted longer.

239
0:43:18,440 --> 0:43:26,350
那国王 他们说那个国王 他独自就杀了960人
The king, they say... They say the king, he killed 960 all on his lonesome.

240
0:43:26,420 --> 0:43:28,520
- 900 吗 - 对啊
- Nine hundred, eh? - Uh-huh.

241
0:43:28,590 --> 0:43:34,030
不过 换成是我 我将会站足够久 开我的弓
Now, if it was me, I'da stayed upright long enough to take my shot.

242
0:43:37,860 --> 0:43:39,230
你的斧子真不错
That's a nice axe you got.

243
0:43:39,300 --> 0:43:41,230
你用那斧子战斗过吗
You do some fighting with that axe?

244
0:43:41,300 --> 0:43:42,940
- 有时候吧 - 在这里吗
- Here and there. - Here?

245
0:43:44,170 --> 0:43:45,740
只在别处
Only there.

246
0:43:45,810 --> 0:43:47,340
在这里 我就是经过
Here, I'm just passing through.

247
0:43:47,410 --> 0:43:48,440
去哪
To where?

248
0:43:48,510 --> 0:43:49,940
我去北方
I go North.

249
0:43:50,010 --> 0:43:52,180
北方 噢
North, oh!

250
0:43:52,240 --> 0:43:54,250
北方是一个方向 很好
North is a direction, all right.

251
0:43:54,310 --> 0:43:55,310
就是北方吗
Just North?

252
0:43:55,380 --> 0:43:56,650
去绿教堂
To the Green Chapel.

253
0:43:58,720 --> 0:43:59,520
噢
Oh!

254
0:43:59,590 --> 0:44:00,590
你知道它吗
Do you know of it?

255
0:44:00,650 --> 0:44:02,590
绿教堂 嗯
The Green Chapel, eh?

256
0:44:04,120 --> 0:44:06,130
那边有条小溪
There's a stream yonder.

257
0:44:06,190 --> 0:44:07,860
它向北湖流去
It runs Northlike.

258
0:44:07,930 --> 0:44:09,830
我是说 如果我 如果我的方位的话
I mean, if I've... If I've got my bearing.

259
0:44:09,900 --> 0:44:11,630
对的 对的 它向北湖流去
Yeah, yeah, it runs Northlike.

260
0:44:11,700 --> 0:44:15,770
但如果你跟着它走一天半 你就会到达一个小教堂
But if you follow that for a day and a half, you'll come to a chapel.

261
0:44:15,840 --> 0:44:17,500
至少我觉得那是个小教堂
At least I think it's a chapel.

262
0:44:17,570 --> 0:44:27,410
它是 嗯 它是 嗯 它总体上不算绿色 但我的意思是 它绝对是带绿色的 有苔藓和 嗯 腐坏物和废墟 但也许就是你在找的
It's, uh... It's, uh, yeah, it's... It's not green on the whole, but I mean, it's definitely greenish, with the moss and the, uh... the rot and ruins, but perhaps it's what you seek.

263
0:44:27,480 --> 0:44:29,480
小溪在那边吗
The stream is yonder?

264
0:44:29,550 --> 0:44:30,420
嗯
Mmm-hmm.

265
0:44:30,480 --> 0:44:31,950
是这条路
It's this way.

266
0:44:32,020 --> 0:44:34,490
穿过田野 与森林交汇之处
Past the field, where the forest meets.

267
0:44:34,550 --> 0:44:37,460
我会找到它 谢谢你
I will seek it out. My thanks to you.

268
0:44:37,520 --> 0:44:39,230
谢谢你
My thanks to you.

269
0:44:39,290 --> 0:44:40,990
走吧
Come on.

270
0:44:41,060 --> 0:44:43,060
我的指向对你一文不值吗
Are my directions not worth anything to you?

271
0:44:43,130 --> 0:44:45,160
谢谢了
My thanks.

272
0:44:45,230 --> 0:44:49,340
我说 我的指向对你一文不值吗
I said, are my directions not worth anything to you?

273
0:44:53,710 --> 0:45:00,480
我是说 像你这样的骑士能够为我这样的可怜虫留下一小点的善举吗
I mean, a knight like you could spare a wretch like me just a small, small act of kindness.

274
0:45:06,450 --> 0:45:08,690
在这 一个善举
Here. A kindness.

275
0:45:08,750 --> 0:45:09,790
噢
Oh!

276
0:45:11,320 --> 0:45:12,660
等等
Wait.

277
0:45:19,330 --> 0:45:21,470
北湖 看到了吗
Northlike. See?

278
0:45:22,940 --> 0:45:24,570
谢谢你
Thank you.

279
0:45:24,640 --> 0:45:26,310
留意溪流
Remember the stream.

280
0:45:26,370 --> 0:45:27,840
我会的
I will.

281
0:45:31,210 --> 0:45:32,780
因为它很狡猾
'Cause it gets tricky.

282
0:45:44,390 --> 0:45:46,560
给你的 孩子
Here you go, boy.

283
0:45:46,630 --> 0:45:48,060
真是个好孩子
That's a good boy.

284
0:45:49,260 --> 0:45:50,600
好孩子
Good boy.

285
0:45:53,460 --> 0:45:55,470
来吧 我们走
Come on. Let's go.

286
0:46:28,730 --> 0:46:30,140
你好啊
Hello, there.

287
0:46:31,100 --> 0:46:32,600
你好
Hello.

288
0:46:41,350 --> 0:46:43,120
看好 看好
Now, now.

289
0:46:51,520 --> 0:46:52,790
- 拜托 - 是吗 拜托
- Please. - Yeah, please?

290
0:46:52,860 --> 0:46:54,730
- 拜托 拜托 - 拜托
- Please. Please. Please! - Please!

291
0:46:54,790 --> 0:46:56,100
- 拜托 - 拜托
- Please. - Please!

292
0:46:59,300 --> 0:47:01,970
拜托 拜托
Please! Please! Please! Please!

293
0:47:05,000 --> 0:47:06,170
拜托
Please.

294
0:47:13,210 --> 0:47:14,280
噢
Oh.

295
0:47:16,120 --> 0:47:17,820
噢
Oh.

296
0:47:20,320 --> 0:47:23,720
还不够 只是还不够
'Tweren't enough. Just 'tweren't enough.

297
0:47:25,760 --> 0:47:27,490
嘿 嘿 你要去哪
Hey, hey, hey! Where you off to, huh?

298
0:47:27,560 --> 0:47:28,760
你要去哪里 骑士的使命吗
Where you off to? A knightly quest?

299
0:47:28,830 --> 0:47:30,660
我不是名骑士
I'm not a knight.

300
0:47:31,530 --> 0:47:32,730
但你说你是
But you said you were.

301
0:47:32,800 --> 0:47:34,770
我从没说过 是你说的
I never said that. You said that.

302
0:47:34,830 --> 0:47:36,040
我从没说过我是骑士
I never said I was a knight.

303
0:47:36,100 --> 0:47:38,300
- 你是吗 - 不 不 我不是
- But are you? - No! No, I'm not.

304
0:47:38,370 --> 0:47:39,810
噢 嗯
Oh. Hmm.

305
0:47:39,870 --> 0:47:41,210
- 好吧 你看着像 - 对啊
- Well, you look like one. - Aye.

306
0:47:41,270 --> 0:47:43,570
闻着像名骑士
Smells like a knight.

307
0:47:53,790 --> 0:47:55,950
- 噢 - 拜托
- Oh... - Please...

308
0:48:06,970 --> 0:48:09,000
噢 噢
Oh. Oh!

309
0:48:11,440 --> 0:48:12,840
啊
Ah.

310
0:48:13,540 --> 0:48:15,010
哇哦
Whoa!

311
0:48:16,210 --> 0:48:17,480
哇哦
Whoo!

312
0:48:17,540 --> 0:48:19,880
耶
Yeah!

313
0:48:24,050 --> 0:48:27,690
那就告诉我吧 那边真有小教堂吗
Just tell me, then. Is there really a chapel?

314
0:48:30,790 --> 0:48:32,160
你就在它里面
You're in it.

315
0:49:07,760 --> 0:49:09,630
哇哦 看这
Whoa! Watch it.

316
0:49:11,100 --> 0:49:12,530
让我拿拿它
Let me hold that.

317
0:49:20,040 --> 0:49:21,870
它适合我
It suits me.

318
0:49:25,440 --> 0:49:26,980
这适合我 对吧
This suits me, huh?

319
0:49:35,150 --> 0:49:37,890
你要好好休息 我勇敢的小骑士
You rest your bones, my brave little knight.

320
0:49:40,930 --> 0:49:43,100
我会完成你的使命
I'll finish your quest for you.

321
0:49:47,000 --> 0:49:48,200
我会好好吃完的
I'll finish it good.

322
0:49:54,070 --> 0:49:56,910
嘿 你要去哪
Hey! Where are you going?

323
0:49:58,440 --> 0:50:00,280
- 嘿 - 嘿呀
- Hey! - Hyah!

324
0:53:32,920 --> 0:53:34,230
格林格洛
Gryngelot!

325
0:55:55,740 --> 0:55:57,040
有人吗
Hello.

326
0:57:08,810 --> 0:57:10,880
你在我床上干什么
What are you doing in my bed?

327
0:57:22,250 --> 0:57:24,120
你在我床上干什么
What are you doing in my bed?

328
0:57:25,420 --> 0:57:26,760
我很抱歉 我 我没有看见你
I'm very sorry. I... I did not see you.

329
0:57:26,830 --> 0:57:28,630
我以为附近没人
I thought there was no one about.

330
0:57:28,690 --> 0:57:30,000
我不是有意冒犯你
I did not mean to offend thee.

331
0:57:30,060 --> 0:57:31,360
等等
Wait.

332
0:57:32,630 --> 0:57:34,300
是我父亲让你来的吗
Did my father send for you?

333
0:57:35,770 --> 0:57:38,540
不 他没有
No. He did not.

334
0:57:38,600 --> 0:57:40,910
我不认识你父亲
I do not know your father.

335
0:57:40,970 --> 0:57:45,080
我只是一个迷路的旅人 在寻找过夜之处 不过我马上会离开
I am just a lost traveler, seeking rest for the night, but I will leave forthwith.

336
0:57:45,140 --> 0:57:46,610
你要去哪
Where are you going?

337
0:57:49,150 --> 0:57:50,550
家
Home.

338
0:57:53,720 --> 0:57:55,290
我回家
I'm headed home.

339
0:57:56,660 --> 0:57:58,390
你迷失了道路吗
And you've lost your way?

340
0:58:00,030 --> 0:58:01,490
是的
Yes.

341
0:58:01,560 --> 0:58:03,530
我也迷失了什么东西
I've lost something as well.

342
0:58:07,300 --> 0:58:08,930
你能帮我找到它吗
Will you help me find it?

343
0:58:12,300 --> 0:58:13,570
你在干什么
What are you doing?

344
0:58:13,640 --> 0:58:15,540
- 我只是 - 别碰我
- I was just... - Do not touch me.

345
0:58:16,470 --> 0:58:18,210
一名骑士应该更清楚
A knight should know better.

346
0:58:35,460 --> 0:58:37,600
你叫什么名字 女士
What is your name, my lady?

347
0:58:37,660 --> 0:58:39,460
我叫温尼弗雷德
I'm called Winifred.

348
0:58:40,930 --> 0:58:42,200
你听说过我吗
You heard of me?

349
0:58:42,270 --> 0:58:43,640
没有
No.

350
0:58:53,240 --> 0:58:54,610
那里
There.

351
0:58:59,280 --> 0:59:01,350
我需要找什么
What is it I'm looking for?

352
0:59:01,420 --> 0:59:02,790
我的头
My head.

353
0:59:05,080 --> 0:59:08,220
你的头在你的脖子上 女士
Your head is on your neck, my lady.

354
0:59:08,290 --> 0:59:10,960
不 它没有
No. It is not.

355
0:59:12,630 --> 0:59:15,300
可能看着像是 但并非如此
It might look like it is, but it is not.

356
0:59:16,970 --> 0:59:18,770
它在泉水处
It is in the spring.

357
0:59:23,810 --> 0:59:26,410
那它是怎么到那的
Well, how did it happen to get there?

358
0:59:28,080 --> 0:59:30,680
一位爵士来寻求庇护 就像你一样
A lord came seeking shelter, like thee.

359
0:59:32,320 --> 0:59:33,820
也许他就是你
Perhaps he was thee.

360
0:59:35,220 --> 0:59:36,490
- 是吗 - 不是
- Was he? - No.

361
0:59:36,550 --> 0:59:37,860
你确定吗
You certain?

362
0:59:37,920 --> 0:59:39,290
是的
Yes.

363
0:59:40,890 --> 0:59:43,000
这位领主想和我睡一起
This lord sought to lay with me.

364
0:59:44,730 --> 0:59:51,300
我击退了他 但他夜晚回来 砸坏了我的门
I fought him off, but he returned in the night and broke down my door.

365
0:59:51,370 --> 0:59:53,510
我想逃跑 但他砍下了我的头
I tried to flee, but he cut off my head.

366
0:59:54,810 --> 0:59:58,540
他把它扔进了泉里 而现在 无论我怎么努力 我都拿不到它
He threw it in the spring, and now, try as I might, I cannot get at it.

367
1:00:01,080 --> 1:00:02,620
女士
My lady...

368
1:00:05,350 --> 1:00:06,720
女士
My lady.

369
1:00:08,250 --> 1:00:10,420
你是真实存在的 还是一个幽灵
Are you real, or are you a spirit?

370
1:00:11,490 --> 1:00:12,890
这有什么区别
What is the difference?

371
1:00:13,990 --> 1:00:15,390
我只是需要我的头
I just need my head.

372
1:00:24,100 --> 1:00:25,870
今年过去之前 我也需要
As will I before the year is out.

373
1:00:36,120 --> 1:00:40,490
如果我进去找到了它 你会给我什么作为回报
If I go in there and find it, what would you offer me in exchange?

374
1:00:41,890 --> 1:00:43,660
为什么你问我这个
Why would you ask me that?

375
1:00:44,720 --> 1:00:46,760
究竟为什么你问我这个
Why would you ever ask me that?

376
1:01:36,310 --> 1:01:38,380
高文
Gawain...

377
1:02:38,070 --> 1:02:39,570
女士
My lady.

378
1:03:06,430 --> 1:03:07,900
现在我能看见你了
Now I can see thee.

379
1:03:08,770 --> 1:03:11,900
我会以我对你的一切关爱将你击倒
And I will strike thee down with every care I have for thee.

380
1:03:14,110 --> 1:03:16,140
绿骑士是你所认识的人
The Green Knight is someone you know.

381
1:05:54,870 --> 1:05:58,370
好吧 如果你想就进来吧
Well, come on in if you want.

382
1:10:41,250 --> 1:10:45,020
嘿 嘿
Hey! Hey!

383
1:10:46,730 --> 1:10:50,030
你要往哪个方向去
Which direction are you headed?

384
1:10:50,100 --> 1:10:52,700
一个疲惫的旅人能站到你的肩膀上穿过山谷吗
Might a weary traverse the valley on your shoulder?

385
1:14:11,700 --> 1:14:13,330
朋友
Friend!

386
1:14:17,470 --> 1:14:18,770
欢迎光临
Welcome!

387
1:15:08,490 --> 1:15:10,420
放松 放轻松
Easy now, easy.

388
1:15:10,490 --> 1:15:12,520
- 你是谁 - 别害怕
- Who are you? - Have no fear.

389
1:15:12,590 --> 1:15:15,060
- 你和朋友们在一块 - 我的衣服呢
- You're among friends. - Where are my clothes?

390
1:15:15,130 --> 1:15:17,760
嘘 放轻松
Shh. Easy.

391
1:15:17,830 --> 1:15:22,300
现 现在是哪天
Wha... What day is it?

392
1:15:22,370 --> 1:15:26,500
是12月21日
It is December the 21st.

393
1:15:26,570 --> 1:15:30,680
噢 别担心 高文爵士
Oh, fear not, Sir Gawain.

394
1:15:30,740 --> 1:15:33,310
你只是睡了一晚
You've only slept through the night.

395
1:15:33,380 --> 1:15:35,250
你怎么知道我的名字
How do you know my name?

396
1:15:35,310 --> 1:15:37,720
我知道的不仅是你的名字
I know more than just your name.

397
1:15:42,250 --> 1:15:44,220
你必须吃东西
You must eat.

398
1:15:44,290 --> 1:15:48,690
新年之际 我要去西部旅行
See, upon the new year, I travel to the West.

399
1:15:48,760 --> 1:15:53,100
一周后 空屋归你
Came you one week hence and an empty home greet you.

400
1:15:53,170 --> 1:15:55,070
不过在那之前 我会去打猎
Till then, though, I will hunt.

401
1:15:55,130 --> 1:16:00,510
我打猎 你休息 这样对我俩都好
I will hunt, you shall rest and we shall both be all the better for it.

402
1:16:01,510 --> 1:16:02,980
啊
Ah.

403
1:16:03,040 --> 1:16:08,010
这位就是我们的朋友 夫人 刚从睡梦中苏醒
And here is our friend, my lady, fresh from his slumbers.

404
1:16:34,240 --> 1:16:42,650
还有这里 朋友 这是你补充体力的早餐
And here, friend, is your breakfast to replenish your strength.

405
1:16:42,720 --> 1:16:45,420
想必 你会需要它
Surely, you will need it.

406
1:16:45,480 --> 1:16:46,920
这是为什么
Why is that?

407
1:16:48,450 --> 1:16:53,090
因为你的英勇 高文爵士 前来面对绿骑士
Because you are brave, Sir Gawain, come to face the Green Knight.

408
1:16:53,160 --> 1:16:58,960
我敢说这片土地上的每张桌子都听说过你 唱过你的歌
I dare say every table in this land has heard of you and sung your song.

409
1:16:59,030 --> 1:17:06,840
高文爵士 最好最高尚的骑士 穿过荒野 寻找他的命运
Sir Gawain, the finest and most virtuous knight, seeking his destiny across these lands.

410
1:17:06,910 --> 1:17:09,210
也许我不是你想象的那样
Perhaps you think that I am something I'm not.

411
1:17:09,280 --> 1:17:12,280
想象的哪样
Such as what?

412
1:17:12,340 --> 1:17:14,450
你打算在这住多久
How long will you stay with us?

413
1:17:14,510 --> 1:17:16,780
我必须在圣诞前履约
I must make my appointment by Christmas.

414
1:17:16,850 --> 1:17:19,650
我会吃完这些 表示感谢 然后离开
I will eat and give thanks and then take my leave.

415
1:17:19,720 --> 1:17:21,420
荒谬 你难道不知道
Nonsense. Don't you know?

416
1:17:21,490 --> 1:17:23,790
绿教堂就在不远
The Green Chapel is not far.

417
1:17:25,390 --> 1:17:26,590
你知道它吗
Do you know of it?

418
1:17:26,660 --> 1:17:28,190
你非常接近那里了
You are very nearly there.

419
1:17:28,260 --> 1:17:30,100
就在河的下游 不到一天的路程
It's down the river, not one day's journey.

420
1:17:33,330 --> 1:17:35,330
你确定那么近吗
Are you certain it is that close?

421
1:17:37,740 --> 1:17:40,410
你抵达终点了 高文
You are at the end of your quest, Gawain.

422
1:17:40,470 --> 1:17:43,740
也许比你预期的早一些
A little sooner than you expected, perhaps.

423
1:17:43,810 --> 1:17:45,680
但目前情况就是如此
But such is the case for us all.

424
1:17:48,480 --> 1:17:50,420
下面是将发生的事情
Here is what will happen.

425
1:17:50,480 --> 1:17:55,290
在圣诞日清晨 我们会送你上路
On Christmas morn, we will send you on your way.

426
1:17:55,350 --> 1:17:59,760
夜幕降临时 你就会站在你命运的入口
And by nightfall, you will be at the doorway of your destiny.

427
1:18:01,430 --> 1:18:03,760
所以就多待一会儿 休息吧
So stay a while. Rest.

428
1:18:05,830 --> 1:18:07,730
享受一下
And make yourself content.

429
1:18:57,820 --> 1:18:59,790
你发现了什么
What did you find?

430
1:19:05,090 --> 1:19:07,960
我从不知道世上有这么多书
I never knew so many books even existed.

431
1:19:08,030 --> 1:19:09,860
你都读过吗
Have you... Have you read them all?

432
1:19:09,930 --> 1:19:11,730
是的
Yes.

433
1:19:11,800 --> 1:19:13,530
我都读过
All of them I've read.

434
1:19:14,700 --> 1:19:18,100
一些由我著述 一些由我抄写
Some I've written, some I've copied.

435
1:19:19,440 --> 1:19:24,410
它们是我所闻之事 是所听之歌
They're tales I've heard, songs that have been sung to me.

436
1:19:24,510 --> 1:19:32,020
我写下它们 而有时 我并不告诉任何人
I write them down and sometimes... Don't tell anyone this.

437
1:19:32,080 --> 1:19:38,590
有时 当我看到改进余地时 我就完成它们
Sometimes when I see room for improvements...I make them.

438
1:19:41,460 --> 1:19:43,860
- 你喜欢书吗 - 是的
- Do you like books? - Yes.

439
1:19:44,960 --> 1:19:47,800
那好 为什么不为你不拿上一本
Well... Why don't you take one with you?

440
1:19:47,870 --> 1:19:49,440
我不能
I couldn't.

441
1:19:49,500 --> 1:19:51,940
噢 但是快到圣诞日了
Oh, but it is nearly Christmas.

442
1:19:52,000 --> 1:19:53,770
这里
Here.

443
1:19:53,840 --> 1:19:55,510
这是给你的
This one's for you.

444
1:20:07,450 --> 1:20:09,020
谢谢你
I thank you.

445
1:20:12,660 --> 1:20:15,690
骑士不该给女士一个吻以示感谢吗
Should not a knight offer a lady a kiss in thanks?

446
1:20:34,550 --> 1:20:36,180
你愿意为我坐着吗
Will you sit for me?

447
1:20:36,980 --> 1:20:38,520
为你坐着
Sit for you?

448
1:20:41,050 --> 1:20:42,290
为一幅肖像
For a portrait.

449
1:20:42,350 --> 1:20:45,160
啊 我已经制作了我的肖像
Ah. I've had my portrait made already.

450
1:20:45,220 --> 1:20:46,660
但不是由我
Not by me.

451
1:21:11,220 --> 1:21:16,120
爱是刺进我心 痛苦的矛
"Ant love is to myn herte gon" "With one spere so kene..."

452
1:21:16,190 --> 1:21:17,360
保持不动
Hold very still.

453
1:21:17,420 --> 1:21:22,860
日夜间我的血干涸 我的心凋亡卷曲
"Nyht ant day my blod hit drynkes" "Myn herte deth me tene."

454
1:21:45,950 --> 1:21:49,660
那是幅很奇怪的画
That's a very queer painting.

455
1:22:06,170 --> 1:22:07,370
那是什么
What's that?

456
1:22:10,440 --> 1:22:11,810
什么
What?

457
1:22:15,280 --> 1:22:16,320
这个
This.

458
1:22:17,450 --> 1:22:18,820
这是一个表示
It's a token.

459
1:22:19,990 --> 1:22:22,020
表示什么 表示祝你好运吗
For what? For good luck?

460
1:22:23,090 --> 1:22:24,120
表示爱
For love?

461
1:22:27,130 --> 1:22:29,230
不是
No.

462
1:22:29,290 --> 1:22:32,230
骑士当然懂得爱
Surely a knight knows something of love.

463
1:22:33,670 --> 1:22:35,070
我不懂
I don't.

464
1:22:36,740 --> 1:22:38,170
真的吗
Truly?

465
1:23:03,260 --> 1:23:04,360
高文
Gawain!

466
1:23:05,630 --> 1:23:07,870
看看我为你带来了什么
Look what I have brought you!

467
1:23:13,040 --> 1:23:16,680
当我驱赶他时 我在想这是多好的礼物啊
When I dispersed of him, I thought what a gift!

468
1:23:16,740 --> 1:23:19,310
给我新朋友的礼物
What a gift for my new friend.

469
1:23:19,380 --> 1:23:20,810
我该拿它怎么办
What shall I do with it?

470
1:23:20,880 --> 1:23:22,950
那 在你的旅途中带上它吧
Well, take it with you for your journey.

471
1:23:24,150 --> 1:23:26,150
你想你说过它在不远处
I thought you said it was not far.

472
1:23:26,220 --> 1:23:29,960
我的意思是之后 你回家的旅途
I mean your journey home, after.

473
1:23:45,240 --> 1:23:48,440
让我们彼此许下承诺
Let us make a promise to each other.

474
1:23:50,080 --> 1:23:53,910
我明天和后天会去打猎
I hunt tomorrow and the day after.

475
1:23:55,150 --> 1:24:00,650
无论森林给我什么 我都会为你带回最好的
Whatever the forest offers me, I will bring you home the best.

476
1:24:00,720 --> 1:24:05,760
而你要回赠我 任何你在这里可能得到的
And you give me in turn whatever you might receive here.

477
1:24:08,230 --> 1:24:12,360
我在这里能得到 有什么不是你的
What might I receive here that is not already yours?

478
1:24:13,300 --> 1:24:15,670
谁知道呢
Who knows?

479
1:24:15,730 --> 1:24:18,970
这屋里满是奇怪的东西
This house is full of strange things.

480
1:24:21,810 --> 1:24:26,850
但话说回来 我在到处都见到不合逻辑的事
But then again, I see things everywhere that bear no logic.

481
1:24:29,510 --> 1:24:32,820
你见过一只鹰杀一匹马吗
Have you ever seen a hawk kill a horse?

482
1:24:34,690 --> 1:24:41,090
就俯冲下来然后 呼 太可怕了
Just swoop down and... Phew. It's terrible.

483
1:24:42,190 --> 1:24:45,360
每个人至少应看一次
Every man should see it at least once.

484
1:24:48,530 --> 1:24:50,270
但世界就是这样
But that is the world.

485
1:24:51,600 --> 1:24:56,170
这个世界容纳了各种各样的奥秘
And the world is fit for all manner of mysteries.

486
1:24:58,880 --> 1:25:02,110
不过 男人的屋子 对所有这些来讲 应该是安全的
A man's home, though, should be safe from all that.

487
1:25:03,320 --> 1:25:08,890
墙挨着墙 齐平 垂直
One wall joined with another, line and plumb.

488
1:25:08,950 --> 1:25:11,460
非常好 坚固的墙壁
Good, strong walls,

489
1:25:13,660 --> 1:25:15,130
还有内部的火源
and a fire within.

490
1:25:16,130 --> 1:25:18,930
为什么他是绿的 你认为呢
Why is he green, do you think?

491
1:25:20,470 --> 1:25:21,570
那个骑士吗
The knight?

492
1:25:21,630 --> 1:25:23,070
是的
Yes.

493
1:25:24,700 --> 1:25:26,510
他生来就这样吗
Was he born that way?

494
1:25:26,570 --> 1:25:30,210
也许这是他脸红时血的颜色
Perhaps it is the color of his blood when he blushes.

495
1:25:30,280 --> 1:25:31,780
但为什么是绿的
But why green?

496
1:25:32,810 --> 1:25:37,620
为什么不是蓝色或红色
Why not blue or red?

497
1:25:37,680 --> 1:25:40,150
因为他不是世间之物
Because he is not of this earth.

498
1:25:40,220 --> 1:25:44,290
但绿色是大地的颜色 生物的颜色 生命的颜色
But green is the color of earth, of living things, of life.

499
1:25:45,630 --> 1:25:48,060
- 还有腐坏 - 是的
- And of rot. - Yes.

500
1:25:49,560 --> 1:25:51,060
是的
Yes.

501
1:25:53,070 --> 1:25:57,170
我们用它装饰我们的大厅 给我们的亚麻布染色
We deck our halls with it and dye our linens.

502
1:25:57,240 --> 1:26:02,240
但如果它爬上了石铺路 我们会把它擦洗干净 尽快地
But should it come creeping up the cobbles, we scrub it out, fast as we can.

503
1:26:04,490 --> 1:26:08,050
当它在我们的皮肤下开花 我们会将它榨干
When it blooms beneath our skin, we bleed it out.

504
1:26:09,720 --> 1:26:29,200
而当我们 一同 发现我们触及的超出了我们能掌控的 我们就将它砍下 将它踏灭 我们在它顶上传播我们自己 把它扼杀在我们的腹下 但它又回来了
And when we, together all, find that our reach has exceeded our grasp, we cut it down, we stamp it out, we spread ourselves atop it and smother it beneath our bellies, but it comes back.

505
1:26:32,610 --> 1:26:36,640
它不拖拉 也不等策划或阴谋
It does not dally, nor does it wait to plot or conspire.

506
1:26:36,710 --> 1:26:42,550
某天将它连根拔起 隔天 它就在那 隐约出现
Pull it out by the roots one day and then next, there it is, creeping in around the edges.

507
1:26:45,380 --> 1:26:49,990
当我们寻找红色时 绿色来了
Whilst we're off looking for red, in comes green.

508
1:26:51,690 --> 1:27:04,370
红是欲望的颜色 而绿是欲望遗留之物 在心里 在子宫里
Red is the color of lust, but green is what lust leaves behind, in heart, in womb.

509
1:27:07,070 --> 1:27:14,280
绿色是当热忱衰退 激情停息 也是当我们死去时 留下的东西
Green is what is left when ardor fades, when passion dies, when we die, too.

510
1:27:21,850 --> 1:27:25,160
你离去时 你的脚印将长满青草
When you go, your footprints will fill with grass.

511
1:27:26,790 --> 1:27:38,000
苔藓将覆盖你的墓碑 当太阳升起 绿色将覆着一切 在它的浓荫中
Moss shall cover your tombstone, and as the sun rises, green shall spread over all, in all its shades and hues.

512
1:27:42,010 --> 1:27:51,120
铜绿将追上你的剑 你的钱币 你的城垛而 尽你所能吧 你珍视的一切都将臣服于它
This verdigris will overtake your swords and your coins and your battlements and, try as you might, all you hold dear will succumb to it.

513
1:27:51,180 --> 1:27:54,520
你的皮肤 你的骨头
Your skin, your bones.

514
1:27:56,860 --> 1:27:58,490
你的美德
Your virtue.

515
1:28:13,410 --> 1:28:22,280
那么你希望收获什么 当面对所有的这 这颜色
And what do you hope to gain from facing all of this... this hue?

516
1:28:24,620 --> 1:28:26,050
荣誉吗
Honor?

517
1:28:27,050 --> 1:28:28,650
你是在问我吗
Are you asking me?

518
1:28:28,720 --> 1:28:29,990
- 没有 - 嗯
- No. - Hmm.

519
1:28:30,060 --> 1:28:31,990
荣誉
Honor.

520
1:28:32,060 --> 1:28:35,260
这就是为什么骑士做他应做的事
That is why a knight does what he does.

521
1:28:35,330 --> 1:28:37,960
这就是你人生中最想要的吗
And this is what you want most in life?

522
1:28:38,030 --> 1:28:39,360
成为一名骑士
To be a knight.

523
1:28:39,430 --> 1:28:40,730
不是 荣誉
No, honor.

524
1:28:40,800 --> 1:28:43,770
你不善于答问
You are not very good with questions.

525
1:28:48,110 --> 1:28:52,480
这是我想要的人生的一部分
It is part of the life I want.

526
1:28:52,540 --> 1:28:55,780
而这 就是这部分所需要的全部吗
And this is all it takes for that part to be had?

527
1:28:57,480 --> 1:29:07,330
你只做了一件事 你回家后就变了一个人 一个可敬的人 就像这样吗
You'll do this one thing, you return home a changed man, an honorable man? Just like that?

528
1:29:08,860 --> 1:29:10,360
是的
Yes.

529
1:29:11,930 --> 1:29:13,300
嗯
Hmm.

530
1:29:16,230 --> 1:29:20,070
噢 我希望能看到全新的你
Oh, I wish I could see the new you.

531
1:29:21,510 --> 1:29:31,450
但也许我们会想念我们的老朋友 我们的乐趣 我们的游戏
But perhaps we will miss our old friend and our fun and our games.

532
1:30:53,070 --> 1:30:54,870
- 夫人 - 嘘
- My lady... - Shh.

533
1:30:57,770 --> 1:31:00,540
昨天你为什么不来我的房间
Why did you not come to my chambers yesterday?

534
1:31:04,110 --> 1:31:05,110
我不能
I couldn't.

535
1:31:05,180 --> 1:31:06,650
你不能吗
You couldn't?

536
1:31:08,050 --> 1:31:09,480
不是 但
No, but...

537
1:31:13,720 --> 1:31:15,190
但你想
But you wanted to.

538
1:31:17,060 --> 1:31:18,360
是的
Yes.

539
1:31:19,790 --> 1:31:21,190
现在呢
And now?

540
1:31:23,430 --> 1:31:28,030
- 我想我能 但是 - 但是 - 这是不对的
- I would that I could, but... - But... - It isn't right.

541
1:31:28,100 --> 1:31:29,530
嗯
Hmm.

542
1:31:30,340 --> 1:31:31,840
是不对的
